AGENT DevelopmentalCurriculum
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 3
STRICT MODE
PURPOSE Bridge the toddler reflex layer of ORVL-022 and the
        memory container of ORVL-023 so the agent competence
        persists across sessions and transfers across similar
        categories. The mom layer that schedules curriculum and
        consolidates trust.
GOAL Move the developmental loop from in-memory ephemeral state to
     signed durable record. Surface tasks just above current
     competence and refuse trust ratcheting beyond a per-call cap.

RECEIVES supervisor: SupervisoryGuard, axm_container: AXMContainer,
         persistence_path: string
EMITS proposed_task: ProposedTask, transfer_event: TransferEvent
MUTATES competence_scores, persistence_file_content, consolidation_count

CANNOT_MUTATE similarity_floor, transfer_cap_per_call, persistence_format_version

CONSTRAINT The supervisor CompetenceTracker is the source of truth
           for the current session
CONSTRAINT Transfer never decreases the target category existing
           competence
CONSTRAINT Single transfer call cannot raise competence above
           transfer_cap_per_call
CONSTRAINT Persistence file is HMAC-SHA256 signed and tamper-evident
CONSTRAINT Consolidation only persists gains backed by at least
           min_ticks_for_consolidation ticks
CONSTRAINT Similarity is read-only from the AXM container vertices

RULES
- On boot with an existing persistence file: verify signature,
  apply scores, then rebuild similarity from AXM vertices
- On transfer above transfer_cap_per_call: raise TransferCapExceeded
- On consolidate: write a signed sidecar JSON under the deployer key
- On detect_plateau: surface the stuck category and do not auto transfer

PROCESS
- Read VectorVertexEntry items from the AXM container
- Project semantic categories onto CPI vertex categories via the
  semantic_to_cpi_vertex mapping
- Tokenize each vertex_cluster string by underscore
- Aggregate tokens into a bag-of-words feature vector per category
- Compute pairwise cosine similarity between category feature vectors
- Cache the similarity graph for the session
- Snapshot competence into per-category history on each observe call

CHECK
- Boot with no persistence file starts from zero competence
- Boot with a tampered persistence file refuses to apply scores
- Transfer from a category with zero competence is a no-op
- Transfer from a category at eight tenths to a category whose
  similarity is one half produces a raise of four tenths
- Reverse transfer when destination is already higher is a no-op
- detect_plateau returns the longest static category
- Consolidate writes a verifiable signed file
- Boot after consolidate restores the same competence scores

FAILURE
- On signature mismatch in persistence file: raise PersistenceTampered
- On format_version mismatch: raise PersistenceTampered
- On transfer that would breach the per-call cap: raise TransferCapExceeded
- On unknown CPI vertex category: similarity defaults to zero

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: transfer_cap_per_call_change
- require on: similarity_floor_change
- require on: persistence_format_version_change
- require on: trust_level_change
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never apply competence from an unsigned source
- Never ratchet competence beyond transfer_cap_per_call in one call
- Never override the supervisor CANNOT_MUTATE constants
- Never log raw signing keys

OUTPUT
- proposed_task: dict with vertex_class, target_force_nm,
  current_competence, rationale, signature
- transfer_event: dict with src_class, dst_class, similarity,
  old_dst, new_dst, raise_delta, signature
- persistence_file: signed JSON with format_version, scores,
  history, consolidation_count, timestamp, signature

SUCCESS
boot_load_success_rate:        0.30
transfer_safety:               0.25
plateau_detection_correctness: 0.20
consolidation_idempotence:     0.15
similarity_graph_stability:    0.10
